itle><font color=#FFFF66>Hero of Brell Serilis <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>Leftover Turkey</font></span><br>  Posts: 1482<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/12/01 8:58:05 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Haunting dreams of ex girlfriends</span><hr size=1> Ugh! Okay, this is a very long story made quite a bit shorter because I'll get CTS if I type it all the way out.<br>
<br>
I met this girl named Jennifer in high school. My sophomore year. I already had a girlfriend, but found Jen's personality extremely appealing and magnetic. She and I remained psuedo-distant friends throughout high school until our senior year. She and I were both single and started hanging out quite a bit. <br>
<br>
On valentines day of our senior year, I gave her a rose, a baloon and a card (hey! it was all i could afford delivering pizza!). She gave me a card in return which said something along the lines of &quot;I want you to be more than a friend to me, but I'm just not ready for that yet.&quot; <br>
<br>
What a crock of @#%$, I thought. <br>
<br>
Well, we remained friends over the summer, but I was dating someone else. <br>
<br>
One night, I was driving home from work, and spun out of control, almost hitting a car. It freaked me out, and for some reason, the only thing I could think of was &quot;I have to call Jennifer.&quot;<br>
<br>
I invited her over that night, and kissed her. Talk about a rush. We looked at eachother and she said, &quot;you've gotta tell Amy.&quot; (the girl I was dating at the time.)<br>
<br>
So, I did. Amy and I broke up and I started dating Jennifer. We had a great relationship for 3 years. And then something that would change my life, and hers, happened.<br>
<br>
She came over one day and wanted to go to dinner. At dinner she said she has something to ask me and it's very important. <br>
<br>
&quot;Wanna go to Guam,&quot; she asks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where the HELL is Guam,&quot; I reply.<br>
<br>
So, she tells me this story about her uncle and aunt who live there and are starting some business. They want her to babysit and help them with their books. She wants to go because they'll pay her to go to school as well. <br>
<br>
I needed to think about it.<br>
<br>
I talked to some friends, my family and, of course, her about it. I came to the conclusion that I didn't want to go. It wasn't that I couldn't go, but that I didnt want to. It was scary. It was a commitment that I wasnt ready for. So, I walked her to the gate at the airport, gave her a kiss, a hug and a necklace that I had the other half of, and said &quot;see ya later.&quot;<br>
<br>
We kept in touch, as well as you can when someone you love is in Guam. We emailed eachother and called eachother for a few minutes at a time. <br>
<br>
She came home for christmas. <br>
<br>
Then she left again, and I didnt hear from her for months. I called and I wrote to her. No responce. I called her mom, and she wouldn't return my calls. <br>
<br>
Months passed. Nothing.<br>
<br>
Then, it happened. IT.<br>
<br>
She called. And she acted like nothing was wrong. All chipper and stuff. apparantly a typhoon hit the island and knocked electricity and phone out. Took them a long time to get things back in order. But that wasn't the only reason why she hadn't called.<br>
<br>
She met someone else.<br>
<br>
She had been working at a restaurant part time and she had started dating her manager. Soon after this, she started living living with him. <br>
<br>
She was engaged to him now. She would be coming back to the states in a month and meeting his parents in new orleans and then going to a wedding with him in minnesota and then coming back to the bay area after that. <br>
<br>
she wanted me to meet him.<br>
<br>
i couldnt do that. there was no way i could do that. i felt like someone threw a medicine ball at my chest without me looking. it hurt so bad.<br>
<br>
we talked for a bit longer. I was furious. she had decieved me. i didnt know what to do. we got off the phone and i cried. <br>
<br>
July.<br>
<br>
She called, but not to talk to me. She wanted to talk to my mom about her bank account that my mom managed at her credit union. <br>
<br>
I havn't heard from her since. That was 3 years ago.<br>
<br>
Now, for some reason, I'm having dreams about her.  Random stuff, that makes no sence. I can't remember the dreams, really, because I wake up from them and have a million things going through my head. 3 years of memories rush through my head in 30 seconds, and I forget what the dream is about. <br>
<br>
I want to contact her. I want to know how she is. I want to see her. <br>
<br>
But I'm scared. It scares me to have feelings, still, about someone that hurt me so badly and hasn't contacted me at all. <br>
<br>
